						               													<description>Sokhazania is a unique game of chance for the whole family, designed to simulate a football match in 15 minutes of game time. It is easy to learn the rules and start having fun immediately.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Sokhazania works on the rule that you will always lose the ball when rolling a 1 or 2, and you will always be able to pass the ball to one of your players or take a shot at goal. If the dice lands out of the box you lose the ball to the other player for a throw-in.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Shots at goal must be defended by the goalie by rolling the dice. If the goalie rolls a 1 or 2 the ball is lost to a corner and the attacking player gets a chance to strike again. If the goalie rolls a 3 or 4 the goal is scored and the game restarts from the centre. A save is made the goalie throws a 5 or 6 and the game restarts from the Goalie Dot.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The player who scored the most goals in 15 minutes is the winner. Extra-time can be played on a draw or the game can be decided with a Penalty Shoot-out.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
